<p style="text-align:left;font-size:16px;line-height:35px;">
  <strong>Hello <%= @email %>!</strong>
</p>

<p style="text-align:left;">
The Travis VCS Proxy user <%= @invited_by %> invited you to the Travis CI VCS Proxy organization <%=@organization%>. 
Travis CI "Version Control System (VCS) Proxy" allows you to connect Perforce Helix Core and Apache SVN repositories to Travis CI and benefit from CI/CD automation Travis CI offers.
</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:30px;text-align:left;color:#333333;">
You must be logged in <%= link_to 'Travis CI VCS Proxy', @vcsproxy_link %> to accept the invitation. If you already have an active Travis CI VCS Proxy account, please log in and use button:
<br>
</p>
<div style="text-align:center;">
  <%= link_to 'Accept invitation', @invitation_link, :style=>'background-color:#2EB459;padding:15px;color:#FFFFFF;text-decoration:none;border-radius:2px;' %>
</div>
<p style="margin-bottom:30px;text-align:left;color:#333333;">
If this is the first time you plan to access Travis CI VCS Proxy, you will receive a separate email with the instructions on how to confirm your account and reset your password. Once you complete these steps, you can accept the invitation using the button above.
</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:30px;text-align:left;color:#333333;">
Once you accept the invitation to the organization <%=@organization%>, you will need to:
<ol>
  <li> Add a repository to your account (please prepare credentials, repository url, and repository name). </li>
  <li> Log in to <a href="<%= @travisci_link %>" target="_blank">Travis CI</a> via the ‘Sign in via Travis CI VCS Proxy’ option and synchronize your account with Travis CI VCS Proxy. </li>
</ol>
<br><br>
Now, you can start building and testing using Travis CI!
</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:30px;text-align:left;color:#333333;">
Read more on <a href="https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/travis-ci-vcs-proxy/" target="_blank">adding repositories in the Travis CI VCS Proxy</a> and <a href="https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/travis-ci-vcs-proxy-get-started/" target="_blank">using Travis CI via Travis CI VCS Proxy</a>. 
<br>
We recommend reading the <a href="https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/for-beginners/" target="_blank">Getting started with Travis CI</a> pages.
</p>
 
<p style="text-align:left;color:#333333;">Thank you, and have a great day!</p>
<p style="font-weight:700;text-align:left;color:#333333;margin:0;">The Travis CI Team</p>